The <strong>HTML <code>&lt;span&gt;</code> element</strong> is a generic inline container for phrasing content, which does not inherently represent anything. It can be used to group elements for styling purposes (using the <code><a href="/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes#attr-class">class</a></code> or <code><a href="/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes#attr-id">id</a></code> attributes), or because they share attribute values, such as <code><a href="/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Global_attributes#attr-lang">lang</a></code>.